64
00:04:28,438 --> 00:04:31,037
It's a nice place with mountains and beaches.

65
00:04:31,038 --> 00:04:34,138
Please do stop by if you're in the area.

66
00:04:34,838 --> 00:04:37,537
So that's why you shamelessly came over.

67
00:04:37,538 --> 00:04:39,238
Shamelessly?

68
00:04:41,138 --> 00:04:42,537
Oh, my.

69
00:04:42,538 --> 00:04:45,637
What's going on? It was smooth riding all the way here.

70
00:04:45,638 --> 00:04:51,237
But why did the suicide of Ms. Kirisaki bother you so much, Kei?

71
00:04:51,238 --> 00:04:53,437
She just happened to be your neighbor, right?

72
00:04:53,438 --> 00:04:54,837
That's right.

73
00:04:54,838 --> 00:04:58,437
They were really good friends.

74
00:04:58,438 --> 00:05:00,537
How did you know?

75
00:05:00,538 --> 00:05:05,537
About a week later, I went to that apartment again.

76
00:05:05,538 --> 00:05:07,437
To check on how you were doing.

77
00:05:07,438 --> 00:05:10,337
But you had already moved.

78
00:05:10,338 --> 00:05:12,637
I had plans to move from before.

79
00:05:12,638 --> 00:05:15,337
Yes, the landlady told me.

80
00:05:15,338 --> 00:05:18,437
That's when I heard about the small fire incident, too.

81
00:05:18,438 --> 00:05:19,837
That's why.

82
00:05:19,838 --> 00:05:21,337
Small fire incident?

83
00:05:21,338 --> 00:05:23,137
There seems to have been a small fire incident

84
00:05:23,138 --> 00:05:24,738
right near the apartment.

85
00:05:25,838 --> 00:05:27,937
Fire! Fire!

86
00:05:27,938 --> 00:05:30,337
Fire!

87
00:05:30,338 --> 00:05:32,937
Where's the fire?

88
00:05:32,938 --> 00:05:34,237
What?

89
00:05:34,238 --> 00:05:37,437
She told me she was surprised

90
00:05:37,438 --> 00:05:38,737
because you came out of Ms. Kirisaki's room.

91
00:05:38,738 --> 00:05:41,437
I went to visit her at her room

92
00:05:41,438 --> 00:05:43,837
but she said she forgot something and went out.

93
00:05:43,838 --> 00:05:47,637
And so, you ended up watching the room for her.

94
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:51,437
Well, I guess you two were close enough to come and go to each other's.

95
00:05:51,438 --> 00:05:53,837
It's understandable that you were shocked

96
00:05:53,838 --> 00:05:56,538
when Ms. Kirisaki committed suicide then, Kei.

97
00:05:58,838 --> 00:06:00,338
Watch out, you idiot!

98
00:06:02,938 --> 00:06:04,537
What's with that look?

99
00:06:04,538 --> 00:06:06,337
Here you go!

100
00:06:06,338 --> 00:06:09,338
Hey, hey. Even kids don't do that nowadays.

101
00:06:12,238 --> 00:06:14,937
But why did the person called Ms. Remi Kirisaki

102
00:06:14,938 --> 00:06:18,337
contemplate committing suicide in the first place?

103
00:06:18,338 --> 00:06:21,237
I asked her that, too.

104
00:06:21,238 --> 00:06:24,037
The day after the article of her committing suicide made the papers,

105
00:06:24,038 --> 00:06:25,838
it seems that a man came over.

106
00:06:26,338 --> 00:06:28,637
Are you sure it's her?

107
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:29,937
Yes.

108
00:06:29,938 --> 00:06:32,437
"Eiji Kamatari (32)" -That debt making non-paying woman

109
00:06:32,438 --> 00:06:35,537
fled in here this time?

110
00:06:35,538 --> 00:06:38,837
In other words, she got tired of running from debt collectors

111
00:06:38,838 --> 00:06:40,437
and committed suicide.

112
00:06:40,438 --> 00:06:41,937
So that was it.

113
00:06:41,938 --> 00:06:45,037
Thanks to you, I finally understand.

114
00:06:45,038 --> 00:06:48,238
No, no. He's just conveying the landlady's story.

115
00:06:49,138 --> 00:06:50,637
I know even more.

116
00:06:50,638 --> 00:06:52,437
It seems that she's been using aliases

117
00:06:52,438 --> 00:06:55,637
since two years ago and fleeing around.

118
00:06:55,638 --> 00:06:59,937
Mayuko Hayashi, Miyuki Wada, Kaori Inuyama.

119
00:06:59,938 --> 00:07:01,537
She's been changing names one after the other!

120
00:07:01,538 --> 00:07:05,437
And even though that brassy woman wouldn't pay off her debts,

121
00:07:05,438 --> 00:07:07,438
she played Pachinko all the time!

122
00:07:07,938 --> 00:07:10,637
She used aliases since two years ago?

123
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:14,637
Then I wonder why she rented that apartment under her real name?

124
00:07:14,638 --> 00:07:16,437
I have no idea.

125
00:07:16,438 --> 00:07:18,337
Besides, Pops.

126
00:07:18,338 --> 00:07:20,737
Calling her a brassy woman,

127
00:07:20,738 --> 00:07:23,237
somehow it doesn't sound like a description of the same person

128
00:07:23,238 --> 00:07:26,137
that Kei and the landlady are talking about.

129
00:07:26,138 --> 00:07:29,137
There's no mistake that it's Remi Kirisaki herself.

130
00:07:29,138 --> 00:07:30,637
The relatives who were called

131
00:07:30,638 --> 00:07:33,738
came to confirm her corpse and take her with them.

132
00:07:34,938 --> 00:07:37,137
Then it couldn't have been a stand-in.

133
00:07:37,138 --> 00:07:38,637
Interesting boy, aren't you?

134
00:07:38,638 --> 00:07:40,938
He's just a cheeky brat.

135
00:07:42,438 --> 00:07:45,038
What's this? A police checkpoint?

136
00:07:47,138 --> 00:07:49,537
We're sorry to bother you

137
00:07:49,538 --> 00:07:52,238
"Tan Yamazumi (35)" -but there was a robbery in the city.

138
00:07:53,238 --> 00:07:56,737
The perp has a mustache, is well-built,

139
00:07:56,738 --> 00:07:58,837
and is fleeing on a white sedan!

140
00:07:58,838 --> 00:08:01,437
He matches the description perfectly.

141
00:08:01,438 --> 00:08:04,237
-What? -You'll get out of the car without resisting, will you?

142
00:08:04,238 --> 00:08:06,138
No, I'm...

143
00:08:07,538 --> 00:08:08,837
Yes.

144
00:08:08,838 --> 00:08:11,037
What? The car was abandoned?

145
00:08:11,038 --> 00:08:15,037
See! Like I told you, I'm the great Detective Kogoro Mouri!

146
00:08:15,038 --> 00:08:16,737
You mean that famous...

147
00:08:16,738 --> 00:08:18,538
I'm... I'm very sorry!

148
00:08:20,838 --> 00:08:22,937
You made it through safely.

149
00:08:22,938 --> 00:08:24,937
Cut that strange talk of yours out!

150
00:08:24,938 --> 00:08:26,738
You two make a great pair.

151
00:08:30,738 --> 00:08:32,937
It'll be at least a two hour wait.

152
00:08:32,938 --> 00:08:36,737
I'll go ask because I know the owner of the place.

153
00:08:36,738 --> 00:08:38,938
No, we can try another place.

154
00:08:42,038 --> 00:08:43,238
That guy.

155
00:09:06,238 --> 00:09:08,937
That's all he wanted to do?

156
00:09:08,938 --> 00:09:11,337
He's crazy to go out of his way to do that.

157
00:09:11,338 --> 00:09:13,537
This sure is a great drive.

158
00:09:13,538 --> 00:09:15,737
You get mistaken for a robber.

159
00:09:15,738 --> 00:09:17,037
Looks like it's going to rain.

160
00:09:17,038 --> 00:09:20,037
It's because we were talking about that apartment.

161
00:09:20,038 --> 00:09:23,037
-What? -That place is cursed after all.

162
00:09:23,038 --> 00:09:24,937
The apartment is cursed?

163
00:09:24,938 --> 00:09:29,337
Real estate agents are the one who usually introduce apartments, right?

164
00:09:29,338 --> 00:09:34,337
But it seems that Remi Kirisaki asked the landlady directly

165
00:09:34,338 --> 00:09:36,737
if there are any rooms available.

166
00:09:36,738 --> 00:09:40,037
I'm sure she was lured to that apartment.

167
00:09:40,038 --> 00:09:43,537
"If you're going to commit suicide, do it here."

168
00:09:43,538 --> 00:09:45,437
I'm sure it was just coincidence.

169
00:09:45,438 --> 00:09:47,937
Kei fell victim to it, too.

170
00:09:47,938 --> 00:09:50,737
She came back here six months ago,

171
00:09:50,738 --> 00:09:55,737
but she was originally planning to come back three months ago.

172
00:09:55,738 --> 00:09:58,137
And she was just about to move out.

173
00:09:58,138 --> 00:10:02,737
My uncle decided to postpone the opening of the resort inn by three months.

174
00:10:02,738 --> 00:10:05,237
You will be jobless if you move out now.

175
00:10:05,238 --> 00:10:08,637
No problem. You can stay here for another three months.

176
00:10:08,638 --> 00:10:12,637
Right! Someone is going to move into the room next to yours tomorrow.

177
00:10:12,638 --> 00:10:13,837
Is that right?

178
00:10:13,838 --> 00:10:15,738
I hope the person's a nice person.

179
00:10:17,138 --> 00:10:19,337
Right after she postpone her schedule,

180
00:10:19,338 --> 00:10:23,837
Remi Kirisaki moved in and committed suicide three months later.

181
00:10:23,838 --> 00:10:26,737
In other words, if things moved along as originally planned,

182
00:10:26,738 --> 00:10:29,937
Kei wouldn't have been involved in something sad

183
00:10:29,938 --> 00:10:31,838
like the suicide of her next door neighbor.

184
00:10:33,138 --> 00:10:35,237
The apartment stopped Kei from leaving.

185
00:10:35,238 --> 00:10:39,637
It made her go through something very sad.

186
00:10:39,638 --> 00:10:41,138
What are you talking about?

187
00:10:42,638 --> 00:10:44,637
It's nothing.

188
00:10:44,638 --> 00:10:46,337
And how did the negotiation go?

189
00:10:46,338 --> 00:10:47,437
It went well.

190
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:51,537
I told him that you were precious guests who came from Tokyo.

191
00:10:51,538 --> 00:10:53,138
Precious guests!

192
00:10:59,338 --> 00:11:01,337
Boy, that was good.

193
00:11:01,338 --> 00:11:03,038
It was delicious.

194
00:11:03,838 --> 00:11:05,437
And Mr. Mouri,

195
00:11:05,438 --> 00:11:08,037
I'd like to show you around here now.

196
00:11:08,038 --> 00:11:10,537
An amusement park! Sounds good!

197
00:11:10,538 --> 00:11:12,638
Nothing tops this.

198
00:11:16,738 --> 00:11:18,338
I'll go get some tea.

199
00:11:19,438 --> 00:11:23,437
Why do they have this stuff in such a rural area like this?

200
00:11:23,438 --> 00:11:26,038
This is a fantastic drive after all, isn't it?

201
00:11:27,138 --> 00:11:29,638
This is the resort inn where Kei works.

202
00:11:31,538 --> 00:11:33,137
But she just said a while ago that...

203
00:11:33,138 --> 00:11:34,938
What's going on?

204
00:11:39,238 --> 00:11:41,937
It was such a clear day until just a while ago.

205
00:11:41,938 --> 00:11:44,637
It's probably just a passing shower.

206
00:11:44,638 --> 00:11:46,638
I hope so.

207
00:11:51,838 --> 00:11:53,637
It really cleared up!

208
00:11:53,638 --> 00:11:56,337
The view is great after the rain lets up, too.

209
00:11:56,338 --> 00:11:59,237
I wish it would keep on raining forever.

210
00:11:59,238 --> 00:12:02,337
What kind of person was Ms. Remi Kirisaki?

211
00:12:02,338 --> 00:12:03,837
Not that topic again!

212
00:12:03,838 --> 00:12:06,637
She's a brassy woman, okay?

213
00:12:06,638 --> 00:12:09,337
Not that. I'm wondering what she looked like.

214
00:12:09,338 --> 00:12:12,237
She had long hair with a perm.

215
00:12:12,238 --> 00:12:13,337
Did she wear glasses?

216
00:12:13,338 --> 00:12:15,137
Nope, she didn't.

217
00:12:15,138 --> 00:12:16,337
Was she fat?

218
00:12:16,338 --> 00:12:18,437
She was rather on the skinny side.

219
00:12:18,438 --> 00:12:19,937
Skinnier than you?

220
00:12:19,938 --> 00:12:21,237
About the same, I guess.

221
00:12:21,238 --> 00:12:24,337
Was she taller or shorter than you?

222
00:12:24,338 --> 00:12:26,537
I think we were about the same height, too.

223
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:27,637
But why do you ask?

224
00:12:27,638 --> 00:12:28,837
That's right.

225
00:12:28,838 --> 00:12:31,038
Just what do you want to know at this point?

226
00:12:36,038 --> 00:12:38,637
It's over there, Mr. Mouri!

227
00:12:38,638 --> 00:12:41,137
It's huge.

228
00:12:41,138 --> 00:12:43,637
No doubt about it.

229
00:12:43,638 --> 00:12:45,638
That suicide was probably...

230
00:12:54,077 --> 00:12:57,577
