00:14:59,977 --> 00:15:02,377
There's no room for evil thoughts.

265
00:15:04,777 --> 00:15:07,476
Thank you so much for everything today.

266
00:15:07,477 --> 00:15:09,176
Not at all. Thank you.

267
00:15:09,177 --> 00:15:11,777
Gosh. There's no more time to think.

268
00:15:13,077 --> 00:15:14,877
He has to drive the car!

269
00:15:16,177 --> 00:15:17,676
Then...

270
00:15:17,677 --> 00:15:19,276
We're heading home to Tokyo!

271
00:15:19,277 --> 00:15:21,976
I can't go home like this.

272
00:15:21,977 --> 00:15:25,276
I'm so full of unanswered questions. I'm jumbled up.

273
00:15:25,277 --> 00:15:26,876
Unanswered questions?

274
00:15:26,877 --> 00:15:28,776
You were planning to come here,

275
00:15:28,777 --> 00:15:31,576
but postponed it by three months.

276
00:15:31,577 --> 00:15:35,076
Then immediately after that, Ms. Remi Kirisaki moved in, right?

277
00:15:35,077 --> 00:15:38,376
Moreover, she did not go through a real estate agent

278
00:15:38,377 --> 00:15:40,876
but by asking the landlady directly in person.

279
00:15:40,877 --> 00:15:43,376
She was using aliases since two years ago,

280
00:15:43,377 --> 00:15:45,576
and yet she used her real name to rent the apartment.

281
00:15:45,577 --> 00:15:48,976
Since her handwriting was left on the rental agreement,

282
00:15:48,977 --> 00:15:52,276
it was concluded that she wrote the suicide note.

283
00:15:52,277 --> 00:15:55,276
So what?

284
00:15:55,277 --> 00:15:58,176
Since her relatives came to confirm the corpse,

285
00:15:58,177 --> 00:16:02,076
it was no doubt that Ms. Remi Kirisaki is the one who died.

286
00:16:02,077 --> 00:16:05,076
But the description of her personality doesn't match.

287
00:16:05,077 --> 00:16:06,976
Remember during the small fire commotion.

288
00:16:06,977 --> 00:16:10,776
Kei came bursting out of Ms. Kirisaki's room.

289
00:16:10,777 --> 00:16:14,576
Obviously, Kei had access in and out of Ms. Kirisaki's room.

290
00:16:14,577 --> 00:16:17,476
Excluding their hair style and glasses,

291
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:19,876
they both have very similar physiques, right?

292
00:16:19,877 --> 00:16:21,876
So what are you getting at?

293
00:16:21,877 --> 00:16:24,476
I can't figure out what's bothering you, either.

294
00:16:24,477 --> 00:16:26,176
The thing that bothers me most is

295
00:16:26,177 --> 00:16:30,577
why you postponed coming back here for three months, Kei?

296
00:16:31,977 --> 00:16:35,876
That's because her uncle postponed the opening of his resort inn...

297
00:16:35,877 --> 00:16:37,976
-But look. -What?

298
00:16:37,977 --> 00:16:40,176
According to what Kei's uncle is saying,

299
00:16:40,177 --> 00:16:42,776
they've been planning to open the resort inn from 10 years ago

300
00:16:42,777 --> 00:16:44,476
during their Silver Anniversary,

301
00:16:44,477 --> 00:16:48,076
and it's written here that they did exactly that.

302
00:16:48,077 --> 00:16:51,776
So the opening of the inn was never postponed.

303
00:16:51,777 --> 00:16:53,076
Which means,

304
00:16:53,077 --> 00:16:56,476
Kei postponed coming back here for three months

305
00:16:56,477 --> 00:17:00,477
because she had reasons on her side for doing so, right?

306
00:17:01,577 --> 00:17:05,176
And something happened during the three months

307
00:17:05,177 --> 00:17:07,176
that she postponed coming back.

308
00:17:07,177 --> 00:17:08,277
Don't tell me that...

309
00:17:09,877 --> 00:17:12,677
But that way, everything falls into place.

310
00:17:13,677 --> 00:17:15,476
Hello.

311
00:17:15,477 --> 00:17:17,976
Yes, I didn't know until the time of the small fire alarm

312
00:17:17,977 --> 00:17:23,376
that Ms. Nakanishi and Ms. Kirisaki were good friends.

313
00:17:23,377 --> 00:17:28,677
Because I never saw the two together even once.

314
00:17:29,777 --> 00:17:31,277
I thought so.

315
00:17:32,277 --> 00:17:37,376
It's no mistake that Ms. Kirisaki hung herself in the room next to yours,

316
00:17:37,377 --> 00:17:39,876
but she never...

317
00:17:39,877 --> 00:17:45,077
No. No one has ever lived in that room.

318
00:17:46,177 --> 00:17:49,576
You've seen through me.

319
00:17:49,577 --> 00:17:53,177
But why did you do something like that?

320
00:17:54,177 --> 00:17:57,676
Out of hate from three years ago.

321
00:17:57,677 --> 00:18:01,176
I had a fiance.

322
00:18:01,177 --> 00:18:03,176
His name was Natsuyuki Ogawa.

323
00:18:03,177 --> 00:18:06,376
When I visited him that day, I found him lying on the floor.

324
00:18:06,377 --> 00:18:08,777
I called the ambulance right away.

325
00:18:10,877 --> 00:18:12,876
But a car was illegally parked

326
00:18:12,877 --> 00:18:17,777
and the ambulance couldn't make it to his residence.

327
00:18:18,777 --> 00:18:20,076
"Natsuyuki Ogawa (29)"

328
00:18:20,077 --> 00:18:22,776
Kei. Kei.

329
00:18:22,777 --> 00:18:26,077
I'm here. I'm here beside you!

330
00:18:27,777 --> 00:18:31,577
He died before reaching the hospital.

331
00:18:32,977 --> 00:18:34,976
I heard that it was already too late

332
00:18:34,977 --> 00:18:37,876
by the time the ambulance got there,

333
00:18:37,877 --> 00:18:42,176
but I still thought that if only that car wasn't parked there.

334
00:18:42,177 --> 00:18:44,276
It was frustrating.

335
00:18:44,277 --> 00:18:46,876
Yes. They never answered their calls.

336
00:18:46,877 --> 00:18:50,376
I had to give the owner of the car a piece of my mind.

337
00:18:50,377 --> 00:18:51,977
But she had the nerve to say...

338
00:18:53,477 --> 00:18:57,976
That guy probably didn't have a long life span, anyway.

339
00:18:57,977 --> 00:18:59,277
Idiot!

340
00:19:04,177 --> 00:19:07,276
And that person was Ms. Remi Kirisaki, right?

341
00:19:07,277 --> 00:19:10,476
She had the nerve to laugh about your fiance

342
00:19:10,477 --> 00:19:12,476
as well as you who just went through losing him.

343
00:19:12,477 --> 00:19:16,376
Then you happened to see Ms. Kirisaki three years later somewhere.

344
00:19:16,377 --> 00:19:19,477
Just three days before I was planning to come back here...

345
00:19:26,977 --> 00:19:28,076
"Anzai"

346
00:19:28,077 --> 00:19:32,676
She was probably using aliases because she was into no good.

347
00:19:32,677 --> 00:19:36,776
I figured that she was not a good woman.

348
00:19:36,777 --> 00:19:38,576
So you thought about it, right?

349
00:19:38,577 --> 00:19:40,776
You couldn't leave Tokyo leaving things as they are.

350
00:19:40,777 --> 00:19:43,976
You had to avenge the death of your fiance who died three years ago.

351
00:19:43,977 --> 00:19:45,176
Yes.

352
00:19:45,177 --> 00:19:46,876
You came up with an idea.

353
00:19:46,877 --> 00:19:49,276
In order for you to run free despite killing someone,

354
00:19:49,277 --> 00:19:52,976
it would be best to set up a suicide.

355
00:19:52,977 --> 00:19:57,776
That's why you suddenly postponed coming back to your hometown

356
00:19:57,777 --> 00:20:00,776
and disguised yourself as Ms. Remi Kirisaki.

357
00:20:00,777 --> 00:20:01,876
What?

358
00:20:01,877 --> 00:20:04,776
Is that room available?

359
00:20:04,777 --> 00:20:07,676
You rented the room next to your own room.

360
00:20:07,677 --> 00:20:11,676
Right! Someone is going to move into the room next to yours tomorrow.

361
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:13,076
Is that right?

362
00:20:13,077 --> 00:20:15,676
I hope the person's a nice person.

363
00:20:15,677 --> 00:20:18,576
You acted as Kei Nakanishi yourself,

364
00:20:18,577 --> 00:20:21,576
as well as played the role of Remi Kirisaki within one apartment.

365
00:20:21,577 --> 00:20:23,776
I really want to die.

366
00:20:23,777 --> 00:20:26,876
Come on, Ms. Kirisaki. Don't say that.

367
00:20:26,877 --> 00:20:28,376
You started dropping hints of suicide

368
00:20:28,377 --> 00:20:30,976
to make everyone get that impression.

369
00:20:30,977 --> 00:20:34,076
That means, during the small fire alarm, you were probably...

370
00:20:34,077 --> 00:20:36,276
Fire! Fire!

371
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:38,676
Fire!

372
00:20:38,677 --> 00:20:41,076
Where's the fire?

373
00:20:41,077 --> 00:20:42,277
What?

374
00:20:42,977 --> 00:20:44,576
You probably took off your disguise

375
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:48,176
and was just about to go back to your room, right?

376
00:20:48,177 --> 00:20:49,476
Yes.

377
00:20:49,477 --> 00:20:52,276
After setting up the background for three months,

378
00:20:52,277 --> 00:20:55,077
you contacted Ms. Remi Kirisaki.

379
00:20:55,677 --> 00:20:57,476
You're using an alias,

380
00:20:57,477 --> 00:21:00,376
but you're Ms. Remi Kirisaki, aren't you?

381
00:21:00,377 --> 00:21:02,176
Who's asking?

382
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:04,477
I'd like to discuss something with you.

383
00:21:05,277 --> 00:21:06,876
You created an appropriate excuse

384
00:21:06,877 --> 00:21:09,977
and secretly took her to the room next to yours.

385
00:21:13,277 --> 00:21:16,577
You made it look like suicide and left a suicide note behind.

386
00:21:17,777 --> 00:21:21,576
You probably phoned the landlady

387
00:21:21,577 --> 00:21:23,676
and told her to get rid of her things

388
00:21:23,677 --> 00:21:26,076
because she wanted to move out of the room.

389
00:21:26,077 --> 00:21:28,376
Exactly.

390
00:21:28,377 --> 00:21:32,377
Are you going to drive me over to the police, Mr. Mouri?

391
00:21:33,777 --> 00:21:34,777
Yes.

392
00:21:39,577 --> 00:21:43,276
The sun's completely set.

393
00:21:43,277 --> 00:21:47,076
It may have set today, but it will come up again tomorrow.

394
00:21:47,077 --> 00:21:48,277
For sure.

395
00:23:18,577 --> 00:23:20,477
"Haido Police Station"

396
00:23:26,677 --> 00:23:29,276
I just brought in a suspect!

397
00:23:29,277 --> 00:23:30,876
Wait a minute!

398
00:23:30,877 --> 00:23:33,576
I cooperated with the police, you know?

399
00:23:33,577 --> 00:23:34,577
Hey!

400
00:23:37,477 --> 00:23:40,377
So it ends up like this after all.

401
00:23:42,177 --> 00:23:43,776
"Next Episode"

402
00:23:43,777 --> 00:23:45,976
Fantastic!

403
00:23:45,977 --> 00:23:48,776
And? What is it, Doc?

404
00:23:48,777 --> 00:23:51,276
There's something good coming up after this, right?

405
00:23:51,277 --> 00:23:53,676
It's almost Christmas, right?

406
00:23:53,677 --> 00:23:57,077
So let's use this 10,000 yen gift certificate.

407
00:24:00,477 --> 00:24:02,776
What... what was that voice just now?

408
00:24:02,777 --> 00:24:03,977
It came from the stairs!

409
00:24:06,877 --> 00:24:08,376
Next Conan,

410
